The paper discusses linear codes and their minimum weight codewords, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and combinatorics (cs.CO). The use of lines in Schubert varieties suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and algebraic geometry (cs.AG), while the construction of orthogonal parity checks and majority logic decoding relates to coding theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SD).
